1
00:00:05,879 --> 00:00:08,146
tapa, tapasyā means

2
00:00:08,146 --> 00:00:13,065
to voluntarily inconvenience yourself
for the sake of spiritual realisation.

3
00:00:13,095 --> 00:00:16,274
[Flowering Fragrance of Devotion]

4
00:00:16,576 --> 00:00:20,771
But now, some taste has come
for those very things

5
00:00:20,771 --> 00:00:23,193
that someone 
was performing previously

6
00:00:23,193 --> 00:00:27,249
out of a sense of following
the order of the Guru or obligation,

7
00:00:27,249 --> 00:00:28,849
spirutual obligations.

8
00:00:28,849 --> 00:00:33,929
Now they have a taste— 
they like hearing about Kṛṣṇa,

9
00:00:33,929 --> 00:00:37,549
they like hearing 
about Mahāprabhu.

10
00:00:38,879 --> 00:00:41,689
ruci then āsakti.

11
00:00:41,689 --> 00:00:43,239
How much do they like it?
 

12
00:00:43,239 --> 00:00:46,719
—You can’t take it 
away from them.

13
00:00:46,719 --> 00:00:49,549
Now they’re attached to it
the way that someone

14
00:00:49,549 --> 00:00:53,799
becomes attached to anything,
they’re attached now to this.

15
00:00:53,799 --> 00:00:55,140
When someone says,

16
00:00:55,140 --> 00:00:58,030
“Oh, I have no taste
for hearing

17
00:00:58,030 --> 00:01:00,840
the Bhāgavatam, the Gītā,
this, that, the other thing …”

18
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:05,190
“Guru Mahārāj said,
“Then stop hearing the Bhāgavatam!”

19
00:01:05,190 --> 00:01:07,340
The person, “No,
I don’t want to do that.”

20
00:01:07,340 --> 00:01:11,180
—“Then you do 
have some appreciation.”

21
00:01:13,785 --> 00:01:21,135
āsakti, then bhāva.
What does that mean here?

22
00:01:21,135 --> 00:01:24,511
this bhāva, that the seed 
of bhakti-latā bij,

23
00:01:24,511 --> 00:01:30,291
sprouted, it blossomed, 
now it’s produced a flower.

24
00:01:30,291 --> 00:01:33,241
That flower has a fragrance.

25
00:01:33,241 --> 00:01:37,821
It means that devotion 
of that particular servitor has a fragrance

26
00:01:37,821 --> 00:01:43,151
that Kṛṣṇa finds as charming
as a sweet smelling flower.

27
00:01:43,151 --> 00:01:48,391
He wants to enhail that more and more.
It’s giving some joy to Kṛṣṇa.

28
00:01:48,391 --> 00:01:54,381
The sort of devotional sentiments
that are manifesting in their hearts.

29
00:01:54,381 --> 00:01:59,805
And when that intesifies
then it expresses as prem,

30
00:01:59,805 --> 00:02:04,086
Kṛṣṇa prem.
Then what?

31
00:02:04,086 --> 00:02:14,416
sneha, man, prāṇaiḥ, rāga, anurāga, 
bhāva, mahābhāva.

32
00:02:14,444 --> 00:02:16,794
But still this is so valuable.
You can say,

33
00:02:16,794 --> 00:02:18,204
“Well, what if someone ...

34
00:02:18,204 --> 00:02:21,634
they only had a brush with this
for a brief time.”

35
00:02:21,644 --> 00:02:23,584
—Still, it’s the best thing.

36
00:02:23,584 --> 00:02:29,384
sv-alpam apy asya dharmasya
trāyate mahato bhayāt
[Bg: 2.40]

37
00:02:29,394 --> 00:02:34,244
Kṛṣṇa says, “Even a small
connection with this will …

38
00:02:34,724 --> 00:02:36,504
trāyate mahato bhayāt

39
00:02:36,504 --> 00:02:41,114
mahato bhayāt—it will save you 
from the greatest fear.”

40
00:02:41,114 --> 00:02:43,899
Which can be interpreted variously.

41
00:02:43,899 --> 00:02:47,819
One place Prabhupād says,
“Resending in the animal species.”

42
00:02:47,819 --> 00:02:49,897
But Guru Mahārāj  said 
in another place

43
00:02:49,897 --> 00:02:56,327
for a devotee the greatest fear is that 
their service is not being accepted.”

44
00:02:56,327 --> 00:02:58,202
It’s very different.

45
00:02:58,202 --> 00:03:00,372
That’s the fear of a devotee

46
00:03:00,372 --> 00:03:04,292
nārāyaṇa-parāḥ sarve
na kutaścana bibhyati
 

47
00:03:04,292 --> 00:03:10,242
svargāpavarga-narakeṣv
api tulyārtha-darśinaḥ
[SB: 6.17.28]

48
00:03:10,242 --> 00:03:14,012
Citraketu said, 
“I only think …

49
00:03:14,012 --> 00:03:18,132
I’m afraid of it’s 
not having any seva.

50
00:03:18,132 --> 00:03:20,002
Doesn’t matter where I’m—
in Heaven or Hell,

51
00:03:20,002 --> 00:03:21,972
I want to service connection.”

52
00:03:21,972 --> 00:03:26,622
That’s what’s important 
to a devotee.

53
00:03:26,622 --> 00:03:31,002
When Śrīla Gurudev came out 
of the hospital in Sokvel

54
00:03:31,002 --> 00:03:34,862
after his operation,

55
00:03:35,312 --> 00:03:39,070
and he thought
he might leave the world.

56
00:03:39,070 --> 00:03:44,256
He came back in 
a very devastated physical condition

57
00:03:44,256 --> 00:03:48,596
and it was also depressing to him.

58
00:03:48,596 --> 00:03:52,686
But someone came forward
for hāriṇam,

59
00:03:52,686 --> 00:03:55,102
and he began to smile.

60
00:03:55,102 --> 00:03:57,362
In the midst of all this pain,
and suffering and misery,

61
00:03:57,362 --> 00:03:58,912
he began to smile,
and he said,

62
00:03:58,912 --> 00:04:03,012
“Oh, they’re still accepting
service from me.

63
00:04:03,012 --> 00:04:06,722
They want more service from me.”
That’s how he interpreted it.

64
00:04:06,722 --> 00:04:08,632
That made him happy.

65
00:04:08,632 --> 00:04:18,192
That cancelled all the misery
of the body, mind, etc.

66
00:04:18,522 --> 00:04:25,932
But we will still conclude
the way what Nārada’s told Vyās,

67
00:04:25,932 --> 00:04:30,622
and what is the line
of Śrīla Saraswatī 􏰅Ṭhākur and his followers,

68
00:04:30,622 --> 00:04:34,612
and what Kṛṣṇa reiterates
in Bhagavad-gītā that

69
00:04:34,612 --> 00:04:39,282
sv-alpam apy asya dharmasya
trāyate mahato bhayāt [Bg: 2.40]

70
00:04:39,282 --> 00:04:49,412
“Even slight connection with this 
is ultimately benefitial for one.”

71
00:04:49,416 --> 00:04:53,766
You can compare it to education,
as Guru Mahārāj once did,

72
00:04:53,776 --> 00:05:01,456
“By pursuing education, there is no guarantee 
that you’ll become Einstein,

73
00:05:01,456 --> 00:05:05,776
but that’s not an argument 
against education.

74
00:05:05,776 --> 00:05:09,846
Still, you’ll become educated
as far as possible.

75
00:05:09,846 --> 00:05:12,224
And you’ll benefit from that.

76
00:05:12,224 --> 00:05:14,944
Same thing with spiritual education.

